               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-279-person2318">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HENRY WALSHAM
               <interp inst="t18300916-279-person2318" type="surname" value="HENRY WALSHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-279-person2318" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-279-person2318" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Between twelve and one o'clock, on the 4th of August, I was passing Staples' Inn, and saw the prisoner coming across the garden, with a basket; I am a bricklayer, and seeing he was a stranger, I asked what business he had there; he said, a man at the end of the street had sent him for his tools - I asked him to go and show me the man - we went, and he could not find him - he then said, "Pray let me go - I have a wife and seven children;" I said I thought I should not be justified, and took him to the Police.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-279-person2319">
                  THOMAS 
                  PERRING
               <interp inst="t18300916-279-person2319" type="surname" value="PERRING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-279-person2319" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-279-person2319" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer, and took the prisoner; he said a man in black gave him 6d. to go and fetch his tools.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been where there were some men at work, and a man asked me to go and open a gate, that I should find some tools in a basket under the trees, and he would give me 6d. to bring them down to him; I met this man, who told me to go and put them back, which I did.</p>
               <p>Witness. He did not put them down.</p>
               <p>
